3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of deep convolutional neural networks. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of residual networks and the optimization of the network model. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the structure of the network model and the effect of different residual block structures on performance.
